text_Original:
5:17 live feed on the left captures the microsmile seen in his right corner of the mouth that transmits delight, surprise, and acknowledgement of the situation while talking, the reproduction on the right tries to capture it slightly too, but it is muted down and ends before fully transmitting the original emotion on top of not showing the lingering aftereffect that is still present one the left that doesn't transmit any emotion but just shows that a smile was present a couple of seconds ago like a shadow that lingers.
This was just an example in the first 5 mins, and only because the side by side was decided to be showcased. 
Tech is good, but has a long way to go if the intention is to replace face to face or real video recordings of people talking without losing things lost like in the small example above. And this even before taking into account the barrier to entry both financially and actual physical effort, moving out and going to get the scan done in the first place.
text_Display:
5:17 live feed on the left captures the microsmile seen in his right corner of the mouth that transmits delight, surprise, and acknowledgement of the situation while talking, the reproduction on the right tries to capture it slightly too, but it is muted down and ends before fully transmitting the original emotion on top of not showing the lingering aftereffect that is still present one the left that doesn't transmit any emotion but just shows that a smile was present a couple of seconds ago like a shadow that lingers.
This was just an example in the first 5 mins, and only because the side by side was decided to be showcased.
Tech is good, but has a long way to go if the intention is to replace face to face or real video recordings of people talking without losing things lost like in the small example above. And this even before taking into account the barrier to entry both financially and actual physical effort, moving out and going to get the scan done in the first place.
